-This is a Java Spring Boot Framework backend project with Layered Architecture.
-Gradle is the ...
-You can see Controller, Service, and Repository(DAO) Layers.
-Client ↔ ︎Controller ↔ Service ↔ Repository(DAO) ↔ MongoDB
-MongoDB has been used and can be setup in Docker. All you have to do is run mongoDb in docker-compose.yml file
-Given entities are User, Timeline, and Moment (BaseEntity and Info are used to eliminate code repetition thus Inheritence has been applied)
-One can benefit from CRUD(Create, Read, Update,Delete) operations thanks to RestAPI
-Swagger is the tool to simulate all operations(one can reach operations thanks to end points)
-Data Transfer Object (Dto) has been used so that some important fields/information can be hidden from the client
-Exceptions...
-Settings...